Marcia Mayaba has joined the Isuzu Motors South Africa (IMSAf) senior executive team as the newly appointed department executive for dealer and business development. Mayaba has more than two decades’ experience in the automotive industry. She has been active in various fields, including truck and car rental, leasing and fleet management, while she also has extensive retail experience as a GM, dealer principal and franchise executive. Mayaba is also the former CE of Barloworld Motor Retail. During her tenure at the JSE-listed company, she also held the position of National Automobile Dealers’ Association VP. Mayaba was voted as one of the Top 100 most influential women in Africa, Automotive Supply Chain, in 2021. “We are excited to have Marcia join the IMSAf team, especially with her wealth of experience, where she will be instrumental in bringing to life the IMSAf vision of transformation, high performance and results,” says IMSAf human capital and corporate affairs senior VP Mongezi Hermans. “The role is both exciting and challenging at the same time,” notes Mayaba. “It aims at bringing about transformation, not only from a diversity and inclusion perspective, but also from the way we conduct business with our business partners and the dealer network into the future.”